This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it focuses on analyzing the content of tweets to discover social identity. It may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) because it deals with social media data. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) because it involves analyzing audio data from tweets. It may also be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) because it involves retrieving relevant information from tweets. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) because it deals with the societal implications of social media data analysis.
